ately collect the policy value and the donor may be entitled to an income tax deduction in the amount of the policy\u2019s value. The donor should consult with their tax advisor.<\/p>\n<h5>Wills:<\/h5>\n<p>The donor may list <strong><strong>A Tail To Tell<\/strong><\/strong>&nbsp;as a beneficiary in their will. The distribution of the estate is then made at the donor\u2019s death.<\/p>\n<h2>\n\t\tDonating Your Time\n\t<\/h2>\n\t<p>The ways in which you can personally help animals is endless. We are each given special gifts; things we really enjoy doing. It is by utilizing this gift that we help make the world a better place for animals. For example, if you like to write, offer to write a grant for the rescue. If you enjoy being outside, please come over and take the dogs outside. If you like computer or administrative work, our to do list in this department is huge. If you enjoy fixing things, we could keep you busy for weeks! So as you can see, the list really is endless.<\/p>\n\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/atailtotell.wpengine.com\/volunteer\/\" target=\"_self\" role=\"button\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tVolunteer\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t<h2>EVERY DOLLAR MATTERS<\/h2>\n<h5>This is what your generous donation can do for the Dogs:<\/h5>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>$10<\/strong> \u2013 Deworming, fecal test, leash, collar<\/li>\n<li><strong>$25<\/strong> \u2013 Vaccination, flea &amp; tick preventative, heartworm test<\/li>\n<li><strong>$50<\/strong> \u2013 Microchip, routine vet visit<\/li>\n<li><strong>$100<\/strong> \u2013 Bloodwork, x-rays<\/li>\n<li><strong>$250<\/strong> \u2013 Spay and neuter surgery, dental cleaning<\/li>\n<li><strong>$500<\/strong> \u2013 Cardiologist work up and exam<\/li>\n<li><strong>$1000+<\/strong> \u2013 Heartworm treatment, major surgery like ACL, eye removal<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong><strong>A Tail To Tell<\/strong> is a 501(c) (3) organization so all monetary donations are tax-deductible to the extent that IRS allows.<\/strong><\/p>